 Cournswood House could almost be Bletchley Park , the English house at the heart of the Oscar-nominated drama The Imitation Game .
The first was wartime Naval cryptographer and Enigma codebreaker Dillwyn Knox , bought it in 1921 and lived there until his death in 1943 .
His memorial stone to Knox can be found bordering the property .
Cournood House is in the south of Buckinghamshire in North Dean .